{"abstract":[{"text":"What AutomixIQ stores locally","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Music Metadata Database","anchor":"Music-Metadata-Database","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the Caches Directory, AutomixIQ keeps a light weight sql database to store the metadata of tracks that have been played for subsequent lookup. This file is called “music.db” and if deleted will be recreated on launch."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Music Analysis Database","anchor":"Music-Analysis-Database","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the Caches Directory, AutomixIQ keeps a light weight sql database to store the analysis data of tracks that have been played for subsequent lookup. This analysis is required to produce beat-matched transitions. This file is called “paralysis.db” and if deleted will be recreated on launch."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Playback Log","anchor":"Playback-Log","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AutomixIQ stores offline playback logs for subsequent reporting on a Core Data database, modelled by the following classes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.SocialRadio\/documentation\/SocialRadio\/AutomixIQPlayLog"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.SocialRadio\/documentation\/SocialRadio\/AutomixIQPlayLogAttributes"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.SocialRadio\/documentation\/SocialRadio\/AutomixIQPlayLogID"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"Transition Playback Log","anchor":"Transition-Playback-Log","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"AutomixIQ stores offline transition playback logs for subsequent rep